In this presidential memorandum issued on July 31, 2019, President Donald Trump designates the Federative Republic of Brazil as a major non-NATO ally of the United States. This designation is made under the authority vested in the President by the Constitution and the laws of the United States, specifically section 517 of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. The memo also authorizes and directs the Secretary of State to publish this determination in the Federal Register.